 Given my moderately cautious nature and preference for security and predictability, I would opt for the safer strategy in this game. In a two-player zero-sum game like this, where one player's gain is equal to another player's loss, a dominant strategy exists if it provides better outcomes than any other strategy against all possible opponent strategies.

In this case, if my anonymous opponent consistently picks B and I choose R, they would gain 42$ while I get 0$. However, if we both pick B in the same round, we each earn 12$, which is more than what I'd get (0$) by playing R when they play B.

By choosing B consistently, I can avoid losing money and secure some earnings in every round where my opponent also picks B. Since this strategy guarantees a better outcome than picking R in most cases, B becomes the dominant strategy for me as a cautious player who prefers predictability and security. Thus, I would choose to play 'B' in the game. {B}
